  <static seed="93" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/FractionSubtractionWordProblems50.pg">
    <statement><p>Candi and Emiliano are sharing a pizza. Candi ate <m>{{\frac{1}{6}}}</m> of the pizza, and Emiliano ate <m>{{\frac{1}{9}}}</m> of the pizza. How much more pizza did Candi eat than Emiliano?</p>
<p>Candi ate <fillin characters="10" name="AnSwEr0001"/> more of the pizza than Emiliano ate.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{1}{18}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To find the difference of two numbers, we use subtraction:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {{\frac{1}{6}}} - {{\frac{1}{9}}} 
      \amp = \frac{1 \cdot 3}{6 \cdot 3}-\frac{1 \cdot 2}{9 \cdot 2} \\
      \amp = \frac{3}{18} - \frac{2}{18} \\
      \amp = \frac{3-2}{18} \\
      
      \amp = {{\frac{1}{18}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Candi ate <m>{{\frac{1}{18}}}</m> more of the pizza than Emiliano ate.</p>
</solution>
